tldr: The user requested a review of a sleep questionnaire application and the
  implementation of missing acceptance criteria. The agent successfully added a
  tiredness severity scale, COMISA detection, insufficient sleep syndrome
  detection, outbound resource links, and weighted EDS scoring to both the web
  and PDF reports.
overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, requesting the implementation of any unfulfilled acceptance
  criteria. The agent proceeded by first analyzing the existing codebase against
  the provided Statement of Work and detailed questionnaire specification,
  identifying several gaps. Subsequently, the agent systematically implemented
  five high-priority features. This included integrating a 1-10 severity scale
  for tiredness, complete with safety warnings, and adding detection logic for
  both COMISA (Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea) and Insufficient Sleep
  Syndrome, along with tailored recommendations. Furthermore, a new section for
  external resource links was added, and the scoring for Excessive Daytime
  Sleepiness was enhanced with weighted calculations. All changes were applied
  to both the interactive web report and the generated PDF report, ensuring
  consistency and adherence to the specified requirements.
